text.__SUMMARY__:
Acacia inceana is a shrub or tree of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.The shrub or tree typically grows to a height of 1 to 4 metres (3 to 13 ft). It blooms from August to September and produces yellow flowers.
There are three recognised subspecies:

Acacia inceana subsp. conformis
Acacia inceana subsp. inceana
Acacia inceana subsp. latifolia
